BREAST-COMPOSITION: Fibro fatty and scattered glandular breast parenchyma (ACR A)
FINDINGS: Large multilayered overlapping calcifications seen in the outer quadrant appear to be postoperative fat necrosis likely. Few small well-defined calcifications seen adjacent to staple pins. Postoperative staple pins are seen in retroareolar region. Diffuse skin thickening with architectural distortion is seen.
